Statistical packages learning

Mohammad Hoseini
Fall 2017

Institute for Management and Planning Studies (IMPS)

Why are we doing this?

To do reproducible empirical research

  • Others can easily repeat the findings using data and codes
    • different from replication: same conclusion in a new study
  • no copy-paste, no GUI use, document everything you do in codes

We focus on R and STATA

  • graphical user interface (GUI) is available for stata & R (Rstudio) but not interesting for us. We want everything coded

R vs. STATA

R STATA
open source expensive
closer to data science (stats/machine learning) commiunity closer to econometricans
package loading structure no hassle, much simpler syntax and module download
powerfull visualization (with ggplot2) simpler visualization
can import many files supports much less formats
poor support of Farsi much poorer in Farsi!
Poor help many online resources better standard help
support of Latex and better reproducibility great GUI
easier writing of programs a shared standard among economists
work much better with big data

By the end of the class, you will learn

How to move from Excel to STATA and R.

How to use a do file in STATA or a script in R to make your work reproducible.

How to manipulate data (combine, merge, summarize, work with string and factor, etc.)

How to visualize data.

How to analyze data.

How to export report to Word, Latex, Markdown, etc.
